            <title>[CAMEL-4794] After restarting route a camel-quartz component fires right away (and it shouldn&apos;t)</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/CAMEL-4794</link>
                <project id="12311211" key="CAMEL">Camel</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;I am adding a new QuartzRouteRestartTest that demonstrates this issue. Not only a message is fired right after restart, but the scheduled times are messed up as well. I tried to keep the fire interval as low as possible, but it has to be large enough to demonstrate the problem. So I went down to 0/5 (fire every five sec), but it&apos;s more obvious with 0/10 or 0/15, the trigger starts firing at the wrong time.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
